statement_latex:
The matrix

\begin{align*}
A = \left[\begin{array}{ccc}
2 & 1 & 1 \\ 1 & 2 & 1 \\ 1 & 1 & 2
\end{array}\right]
\end{align*}

is known to have eigenvalues 1 and 4.

\textbf{(a)} Find the eigenvector of \emph{A} that corresponds to
eigenvalue 4.
